      "name": "Medical Cannabis Card Status",
      "code": "PX511201",
      "abbreviation": "PX511201",
      "description": "This questionnaire includes two items from the International Cannabis Policy Study Survey, Wave 6 (2023). Respondents are first asked whether they have received a recommendation for medical cannabis and then whether they have a medical marijuana card.",
      "domain": "Substance Use",
      "citation": "Corsetti, D., Fataar, F., Burkalter, R., Hammond, D. (2023). International Cannabis Policy Study Technical Report-Wave 5 (2022). Waterloo, Ontario, Canada: University of Waterloo. http://cannabisproject.ca/methods/ Hammond, D., Goodman, S., Wadsworth, E., Rynard, V., Boudreau, C., & Hall, W. (2020). Evaluating the impacts of cannabis legalization: The International Cannabis Policy Study. International Journal on Drug Policy, 77 , 102698. https://doi.org/10.1016/j.drugpo.2020.102698 [PhenX: https://www.phenxtoolkit.org/protocols/view/511201]",
